data.name: label20.ToolTip
data.value: Number of total digtis (including decimals) that will be shown, per example if the Bitcoin has a price of 1234.56789 USD, by setting this feature to 7 and Max Decimals to 2 it will show only 1234.56, however setting Max Decimals to 4 it will show 1234,567 instead of 1234,5678 (because the digit limit is 7).

data.name: buttonCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Makes a request with each coin to ensures that everything is correct, this is because little amount of coins only accepts a very specific conversion (highly recommended when adding a new coin or swapping the target coin)
